{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Withhold financial support to employers making staff redundant during Covid-19",
        "additional_details": "The Government should withhold any form of support \u2013 including grants, loans, guarantees and reliefs \u2013 from businesses that make lay offs or redundancies rather than access the Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme . It would be unfair for these companies to receive Government support when they are failing to protect their employees.",
        "background": "The Government has established the Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme to enable employers to keep staff on during the Covid-19 outbreak, but some employers are instead laying off staff or making them redundant, and not taking up the scheme.",
